WELCOME TO RANCHO LOS ALAMITOS

A Place For All Time

Welcome to Rancho Los Alamitos!

A Place For All Time


THE MISSION of Rancho Los Alamitos is to educate and engage visitors by sharing our rich history, compelling stories, and authentic connections to California’s past, thus inspiring a sense of community.

Discover the Magic of the Rancho
The historic ranch house and gardens in Long Beach, California is open to the public at no charge and for all people to enjoy. Come and immerse yourself in the history and beauty of Rancho Los Alamitos.

​UPCOMING PROGRAMS
Exploration Talk Series
February 26, April 23, June 25, August 27, and October 22
​from 6:00 PM - 7:00 PM 
Tickets go on sale soon for February 26th

This series explores a range of topics focusing on environmental, multicultural, and historical issues. Presented by experts in the field, these presentations will ignite curiosity and foster a deeper connection to the world around us. 

Visit The Gardens of Rancho Los Alamitos

The Gardens

The four acres of historic gardens at Rancho Los Alamitos date from the late 19th and early 20th centuries.
